#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:5
msgid "Building Emscripten from Source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:7
msgid ""
"Building Emscripten yourself is an alternative to getting binaries using the "
"emsdk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:10
msgid ""
"Emscripten itself is written in Python and JavaScript so it does not need to "
"be compiled.  However, after checkout you will need to run the top level "
"``bootstrap.py`` script before the toolchain is usable.  This performs "
"various steps including ``npm install`` and the creation of compiler entry "
"points (e.g. `.bat` files on windows)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:16
msgid ""
"Emscripten comes with its own versions of some C/C++ system libraries which "
"``emcc`` builds automatically as and when needed (in the emsdk builds, these "
"are precompiled). You can also build them manually with the ``embuilder`` "
"tool - see ``embuilder --help`` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:21
msgid ""
"In addition to the main emscripten repository you will also need to checkout "
"and build LLVM and Binaryen (as detailed below).  After compiling these, you "
"will need to edit your ``.emscripten`` file to point to their corresponding "
"locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:26
msgid ""
"Use the ``main`` branches of each of these repositories, or check the "
"`Packaging <https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/blob/main/docs/"
"packaging.md>`_ instructions to identify precise commits used in a specific "
"release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:32
msgid "Building LLVM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:34
msgid ""
"Build LLVM from the `git repo <https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project>`_. "
"Include clang and wasm-ld (using something like ``-"
"DLLVM_ENABLE_PROJECTS='lld;clang'``) and the Wasm backend (which is included "
"by default; just don't disable it), following `that project's instructions "
"<http://llvm.org/docs/CMake.html>`_. For example, something like this can "
"work:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:45
msgid ""
"Then set the environment variable ``EM_LLVM_ROOT`` to ``<llvm_src>/build/"
"bin`` (no need to install)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:47
msgid ""
"If you need to match the emsdk releases of LLVM, `review the emscripten-"
"release build and test scripts <https://chromium.googlesource.com/emscripten-"
"releases/+/refs/heads/main#build-and-test-scripts-in>`_. Specifically `src/"
"build.py <https://chromium.googlesource.com/emscripten-releases/+/refs/heads/"
"main/src/build.py>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:51
msgid "Please refer to the upstream docs for more detail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:54
msgid "Building Binaryen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/index.rst:56
msgid ""
"See the `Binaryen build instructions <https://github.com/WebAssembly/"
"binaryen#building>`_."
msgstr ""
